                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-06-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 7, 1906</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(The chargé d’affaires of Great Britain informs Mr. Rockhill that the Chinese
                    Government declares that the decree appointing the high commissioners makes no
                    change in the administration of the maritime customs, which, it is stipulated,
                    shall remain as at present constituted during the currency of the loans of 1896
                    and 1898. The Government of Great Britain has declared its satisfaction.)</p>
            </div>
